523
00:40:47,419 --> 00:40:50,470
You'd get to sleep an extra 2-3 hours, you know.

524
00:40:55,300 --> 00:40:57,979
I'm just a bit tired. It's really not a big deal.

525
00:40:57,979 --> 00:41:00,630
If it makes you not lonely...

526
00:41:01,420 --> 00:41:05,799
and you can smile... then my tiredness will go away.

527
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:15,400
Hey, I'm a grown-up now.

528
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,353
I'll live.

529
00:41:18,140 --> 00:41:21,019
Do we have to stick together every day or something?

530
00:41:21,019 --> 00:41:23,770
We wouldn't be able to make a living or anything.

531
00:41:25,100 --> 00:41:27,450
When the play is over,

532
00:41:27,450 --> 00:41:30,100
we'll get to be together for a long time.

533
00:41:37,220 --> 00:41:39,139
You really want that?

534
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:46,630
It's not that far. The taxi fee is only a few hundred baht.

535
00:41:47,180 --> 00:41:49,230
If I can't handle it,

536
00:41:50,260 --> 00:41:52,420
I'll come see you.

537
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:03,393
Do you love me?

538
00:42:03,820 --> 00:42:05,853
Why do you ask?

539
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:10,479
Do you love me? Do you love me? Do you love me?

540
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:15,680
Do you love me? Do you, do you, do you?

541
00:42:20,580 --> 00:42:22,413
I love you.

542
00:42:22,860 --> 00:42:24,693
I love you very much.

543
00:42:30,100 --> 00:42:32,400
That's all that matters.

544
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:48,719
I think I'm gonna choose Films as my major. How about you, Oh-aew?

545
00:42:48,719 --> 00:42:50,959
Well... I think I'm gonna choose Performing Arts.

546
00:42:50,959 --> 00:42:53,379
Oh, that's nice. If I start filming, I'll have you as my actor.

547
00:42:53,379 --> 00:42:54,860
Sure.

548
00:42:54,860 --> 00:42:57,859
And are you going somewhere now?

549
00:42:57,859 --> 00:42:59,810
Want to get lunch together?

550
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:02,353
Fon!

551
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:08,319
The thing is... I already made plans with some friends from my old school.

552
00:43:08,319 --> 00:43:09,639
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

553
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:11,440
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

554
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:10,620
[Oh-aew: Mod, you wanna eat dinner together this evening?]

555
00:44:10,620 --> 00:44:15,380
[Mod: I can't. There's a thing at my faculty.]

556
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:23,139
[Mom]

557
00:44:23,139 --> 00:44:27,379
Oh, dear, it's been busy. Lots of storms coming.

558
00:44:27,379 --> 00:44:31,499
Last night, a water pump broke. It was hectic until this morning.

559
00:44:31,499 --> 00:44:33,339
In Bangkok, there's no rain at all, Mom.

560
00:44:33,339 --> 00:44:38,679
Oh, it's good that it's not raining. That way, it won't be difficult to get to school.

561
00:44:38,679 --> 00:44:40,619
Also, do you want anything else to eat?

562
00:44:40,619 --> 00:44:42,239
I'll send it to you.

563
00:44:42,239 --> 00:44:46,060
Geez! The food here in Bangkok is so much better.

564
00:44:46,060 --> 00:44:48,620
Well, well... All right, Oh-aew!

565
00:44:48,620 --> 00:44:51,190
I'll call you again tomorrow, okay?

566
00:44:51,199 --> 00:44:52,859
I have to go to bed early tonight.

567
00:44:52,859 --> 00:44:55,859
Your dad and I will go to Khao Lak tomorrow.

568
00:44:55,859 --> 00:44:59,859
Well, well... Your son isn't there and the two of you are sneaking off on a trip, huh?

569
00:44:59,859 --> 00:45:01,973
That's right!

570
00:45:02,520 --> 00:45:04,039
Oh-aew, you too.

571
00:45:04,039 --> 00:45:07,240
Go to sleep already. Otherwise you'll wake up late tomorrow.

572
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:09,990
All right. I'll talk to you later.

573
00:45:32,940 --> 00:45:36,039
♫ Tonight, the night is so long ♫

574
00:45:36,039 --> 00:45:40,140
♫ But I guess it's all right ♫

575
00:45:40,140 --> 00:45:45,700
♫ Because tonight, all my heart still belongs to you ♫

576
00:45:48,580 --> 00:45:51,739
♫ I still feel lonely sometimes ♫

577
00:45:51,739 --> 00:45:54,819
♫ But tonight I'm still waiting to see you ♫

578
00:45:54,819 --> 00:46:01,560
♫ Just for you to say "Sweet dreams" ♫

579
00:46:47,700 --> 00:46:50,180
Are you... a freshman?

580
00:46:51,060 --> 00:46:52,939
Can I sit here with you?

581
00:46:52,939 --> 00:46:54,973
Sure, go ahead.

582
00:47:01,780 --> 00:47:03,059
What time are we supposed to meet up today?

583
00:47:03,059 --> 00:47:04,460
11 a.m.! And what time did you come?

584
00:47:04,460 --> 00:47:06,599
Noon! We could've eaten out.

585
00:47:06,599 --> 00:47:08,839
Look! Now we have to eat here at the canteen! Damn it!

586
00:47:08,839 --> 00:47:10,979
Mangpong, can you not complain so much. Next time, just don't wait for me.

587
00:47:10,979 --> 00:47:12,379
If I don't wait, you'll throw a fuss again.

588
00:47:12,379 --> 00:47:15,539
- Q, your water.
- Oh, yeah, thank you.

589
00:47:15,539 --> 00:47:17,770
- Let me try some.
- Go for it.

590
00:47:19,540 --> 00:47:21,273
Want to eat some?

591
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:24,239
Here.

592
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:25,673
Go ahead and eat it.

593
00:47:27,700 --> 00:47:28,659
I want to eat some, too.

594
00:47:28,659 --> 00:47:29,860
No, you can't have it.

595
00:47:29,860 --> 00:47:31,493
Damn...

596
00:47:34,740 --> 00:47:37,299
Oh right, I'm Q.

597
00:47:37,299 --> 00:47:38,780
And this is Plug.

598
00:47:38,780 --> 00:47:41,460
Mangpong. And finally, Auu.

599
00:47:43,740 --> 00:47:46,199
You don't have to be polite with us.

600
00:47:46,199 --> 00:47:48,139
Except for this pug-like dog, Plug.

601
00:47:48,139 --> 00:47:50,940
He doesn't curse. Can you believe that?

602
00:47:51,900 --> 00:47:54,839
All right, so I won't use impolite words with Plug.

603
00:47:54,839 --> 00:47:57,239
No, no, no. He doesn't curse with us.

604
00:47:57,239 --> 00:48:00,339
But we can curse at him. Use all the curse words you want.

605
00:48:00,339 --> 00:48:02,273
Ai'Shithead Plug. See?

606
00:48:03,900 --> 00:48:07,479
So, we don't have to be so polite to each other, right?

607
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:10,600
What's your name?

608
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:13,239
Oh-aew.

609
00:48:14,220 --> 00:48:15,979
Oh-ae?

610
00:48:15,979 --> 00:48:16,939
Oh-aew.

611
00:48:16,939 --> 00:48:18,319
Oh-aew.

612
00:48:18,319 --> 00:48:20,819
- Oh-aew.
- Oh-aew.

613
00:48:20,819 --> 00:48:22,759
Can we just call you Aew?

614
00:48:22,759 --> 00:48:24,700
Aew-aew. Aew-aew. Something like this?

615
00:48:24,700 --> 00:48:28,050
Aew-aew, your ass. Are you a seal or what?

616
00:48:28,900 --> 00:48:30,879
So what does Oh-aew mean?

617
00:48:30,879 --> 00:48:33,599
It's a name of a dessert in Phuket.

618
00:48:34,420 --> 00:48:36,270
What kind of dessert?

619
00:48:39,180 --> 00:48:43,239
Well, Oh Aew is a kind of jelly.

620
00:48:43,239 --> 00:48:46,060
Made of Oh Aew seeds.

621
00:48:46,060 --> 00:48:49,380
It's kind of like shaved ice.

622
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:54,440
You put red syrup on it.

623
00:48:54,440 --> 00:48:57,160
And grass jelly...

624
00:48:57,160 --> 00:48:59,320
and red beans...

625
00:49:15,780 --> 00:49:17,813
It's yummy.

626
00:49:19,860 --> 00:49:22,080
It's really yummy...

627
00:49:23,220 --> 00:49:26,400
Hey. What's wrong?

628
00:49:33,660 --> 00:49:37,519
Sorry. Sorry, man. I'm all right.

629
00:49:41,620 --> 00:49:45,680
Well then, are you going somewhere?

630
00:49:49,440 --> 00:49:51,440
Do you want to come with us?

631
00:49:53,220 --> 00:49:54,900
Let's go together.

632
00:49:54,900 --> 00:49:56,633
Yeah, let's go.

633
00:49:58,960 --> 00:49:59,959
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

634
00:49:59,960 --> 00:50:02,759
- You'll go, right?
- Let's go together.

635
00:50:05,140 --> 00:50:07,900
Bombs away!

636
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:11,300
Geez, Asshole.

637
00:50:16,980 --> 00:50:19,699
My house only has a bingsu maker...

638
00:50:19,699 --> 00:50:22,550
Don't know if it's gonna be as good as Oh Aew.

639
00:50:28,740 --> 00:50:30,790
Still, I guess it's all right.

640
00:50:30,790 --> 00:50:33,320
You "guess"? That means it's not, right?

641
00:50:34,140 --> 00:50:36,073
It's great.

642
00:50:46,380 --> 00:50:51,359
Getting homesick is normal. You'll get over it.

643
00:50:51,359 --> 00:50:53,720
I've been there.

644
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:56,799
You've been homesick before?

645
00:50:57,880 --> 00:50:59,880
When I was an exchange student in India.

646
00:51:03,980 --> 00:51:08,079
And you... did you come here from Phuket by yourself?

647
00:51:08,079 --> 00:51:10,260
Did any friends come with you?

648
00:51:11,980 --> 00:51:16,099
I have friends who came too, but they're in different faculties.

649
00:51:16,920 --> 00:51:21,470
And there's my partner that came, too. He's in Communication Arts at Prachayanan.

650
00:51:22,460 --> 00:51:26,799
And... your boyfriend isn't staying with you?

651
00:51:29,820 --> 00:51:32,459
Well, it's the period when we're adjusting to our new faculties.

652
00:51:32,459 --> 00:51:34,960
Everyone's been busy.

653
00:51:36,460 --> 00:51:38,659
I don't want to bother anyone.

654
00:51:38,659 --> 00:51:42,410
I think... I'll just miss my home for a bit. I'll be over it soon.

655
00:51:47,440 --> 00:51:49,279
Well, how about this?

656
00:51:49,279 --> 00:51:52,299
Even though my home might not have a beach like yours,

657
00:51:52,299 --> 00:51:54,179
there's a swimming pool.

658
00:51:54,179 --> 00:51:55,759
If you want to play in the water,

659
00:51:55,759 --> 00:51:57,979
or if you get lonely again,

660
00:51:57,979 --> 00:52:00,880
just think of this place as your home, too.

661
00:52:00,880 --> 00:52:03,790
You can always come by, no worries.

662
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:07,179
Hey, what are you eating?

663
00:52:07,179 --> 00:52:08,119
- Is that bingsu?
- Bingsu?

664
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:09,319
I want to eat it, too!

665
00:52:09,320 --> 00:52:11,639
- I wanna eat it, too.
- I wanna eat it, too.

666
00:52:11,640 --> 00:52:12,959
Give me some.

667
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:15,079
- I want to eat some, too.
- You don't need to eat it!

668
00:52:15,080 --> 00:52:17,140
I just want to eat some.

669
00:52:18,260 --> 00:52:21,780
[One Month Later]

670
00:52:37,000 --> 00:52:39,760
[Q: What time are you coming to my place today?]

671
00:52:45,680 --> 00:52:48,180
[Oh-aew: I'll watch the play first. I'll go soon.]

672
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:53,140
Hello, I'm here.

673
00:52:53,140 --> 00:52:55,759
Sorry, Oh. The backstage work has been really hectic.

674
00:52:55,759 --> 00:52:57,679
I probably won't be able to go greet you.

675
00:52:57,679 --> 00:53:01,440
Oh, come on. I want to see your face.

676
00:53:01,440 --> 00:53:05,139
Then, can you like get on the stage for a bit?

677
00:53:05,139 --> 00:53:07,940
If I do that, they'll scold me to death.

678
00:53:10,340 --> 00:53:11,739
If you want to see my face...

679
00:53:11,739 --> 00:53:12,979
When P'Top says,

680
00:53:12,979 --> 00:53:14,840
"Fix your eyes on the pendulum,"

681
00:53:14,840 --> 00:53:17,990
you close your eyes for ten seconds and then open them.

682
00:53:19,140 --> 00:53:20,979
What will P'Top say again?

683
00:53:20,979 --> 00:53:24,340
"Fix your eyes on the pendulum."

684
00:53:25,840 --> 00:53:27,619
And why do I have to close my eyes?

685
00:53:27,619 --> 00:53:29,959
Well, just do it, okay?

686
00:53:29,959 --> 00:53:32,800
I gotta go now. I'll see you soon.

687
00:53:36,820 --> 00:53:38,739
It's been three months, three whole months.

688
00:53:38,739 --> 00:53:40,899
I've tried sleeping pills, relaxing massage,

689
00:53:40,899 --> 00:53:42,339
playing sports in the late morning,

690
00:53:42,339 --> 00:53:44,539
keeping a sleep schedule, listening to ASMR,

691
00:53:44,539 --> 00:53:46,219
moving to sleep on the sofa,

692
00:53:46,219 --> 00:53:47,919
on the ceiling, and on the roof.

693
00:53:47,920 --> 00:53:49,900
But no matter what I do, I can't fall asleep.

694
00:53:49,900 --> 00:53:53,139
What should I do in order to be able to sleep?

695
00:53:53,840 --> 00:53:56,979
You've tried sleeping pills, relaxing massage,

696
00:53:56,979 --> 00:53:58,340
playing sports in the late morning,

697
00:53:58,340 --> 00:53:59,719
keeping a sleep schedule,

698
00:53:59,719 --> 00:54:01,219
listening to ASMR,

699
00:54:01,219 --> 00:54:02,580
moving to sleep on the sofa,

700
00:54:02,580 --> 00:54:05,680
on the ceiling, and on a roof.

701
00:54:05,680 --> 00:54:08,400
but... you still can't sleep?

702
00:54:13,140 --> 00:54:15,699
Have you tried closing your eyes yet?

703
00:54:15,699 --> 00:54:19,459
I've tried it already. But even when I do, I can't sleep.

704
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:23,240
Then can you close your eyes for me?

705
00:54:24,320 --> 00:54:26,719
See? I've closed them,

706
00:54:26,719 --> 00:54:29,380
but I still feel like I haven't.

707
00:54:33,220 --> 00:54:35,300
Then let me try.

708
00:54:36,540 --> 00:54:39,220
Look at this pendulum.

709
00:54:39,220 --> 00:54:41,720
Don't fix your gaze anywhere else.

710
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:54,140
Try fixing your eyes on the pendulum.

711
00:54:56,460 --> 00:54:59,420
"Fix your eyes on the pendulum."

712
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:03,660
"Fix your eyes on the pendulum."

713
00:55:13,380 --> 00:55:14,539
One.

714
00:55:14,539 --> 00:55:15,819
Two.

715
00:55:15,819 --> 00:55:17,179
Three.

716
00:55:17,179 --> 00:55:21,139
- Four. Five. Six.
- I think I'm getting sleepy.

717
00:55:21,139 --> 00:55:22,419
Seven.

718
00:55:22,419 --> 00:55:25,870
- Eight. Nine...
- I'll go to sleep now.

719
00:55:25,870 --> 00:55:27,553
Ten.

720
00:55:58,740 --> 00:56:02,330
Ai Teh, what the hell did you do? Don't think that I didn't see that.

721
00:56:36,060 --> 00:56:37,693
Boo!

722
00:56:46,760 --> 00:56:48,659
I thought you wanted me to see something.

723
00:56:48,659 --> 00:56:52,019
You just had me see a guy running in the dark.

724
00:56:52,019 --> 00:56:55,359
Well, I wanted you to see me on stage.

725
00:56:56,460 --> 00:56:58,193
Here.

726
00:56:59,380 --> 00:57:01,800
For your first play.

727
00:57:04,660 --> 00:57:07,659
Hey, I'm only a backstage hand.

728
00:57:07,659 --> 00:57:09,779
Do I get flowers as well?

729
00:57:09,779 --> 00:57:11,413
Yeah.

730
00:57:20,340 --> 00:57:22,273
Thank you.

731
00:57:25,460 --> 00:57:27,819
The play's finally over, so now I...

732
00:57:27,819 --> 00:57:30,920
can go back to spending every night with you, right?

733
00:57:36,000 --> 00:57:38,620
Getting shy?

734
00:57:42,880 --> 00:57:44,499
Excuse me.

735
00:57:44,499 --> 00:57:45,999
Who's this?

736
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:49,580
Could you please introduce your friend to us?

737
00:57:49,580 --> 00:57:51,639
Oh, this is Oh-aew.

738
00:57:54,240 --> 00:57:57,199
Oh, the one that's not a friend, but a...

739
00:57:57,200 --> 00:57:59,700
a boyfriend, maybe?

740
00:58:00,860 --> 00:58:04,100
You're studying Communication Arts at Anantasart, right?

741
00:58:04,100 --> 00:58:05,879
That's right.

742
00:58:06,660 --> 00:58:09,560
Oh-aew, that's not a very common name, is it?

743
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:12,300
That's true.

744
00:58:12,300 --> 00:58:14,479
This is P'Khim, the director.

745
00:58:14,479 --> 00:58:17,179
- And this is P'Jai, the stage manager.
- Hello.

746
00:58:17,179 --> 00:58:19,260
- Hello.
- Hello.

747
00:58:19,260 --> 00:58:21,959
Oh, yeah! I almost forgot. I have something to tell you.

748
00:58:21,959 --> 00:58:22,839
Yes.

749
00:58:22,839 --> 00:58:25,279
This play has been nominated for the contest.

750
00:58:25,279 --> 00:58:26,859
But we only got one month.

751
00:58:26,859 --> 00:58:29,219
So I think I'll fix it as good as it can get.

752
00:58:29,219 --> 00:58:30,579
Let's have a meeting.

753
00:58:30,579 --> 00:58:32,980
Here, right after clearing the set, we'll go out for a meal.

754
00:58:32,980 --> 00:58:36,560
That way we can have a long meeting and talk about it. Okay?

755
00:58:37,860 --> 00:58:41,020
Oh-aew, you can join us.

756
00:58:41,020 --> 00:58:43,330
Because there's only us and just a few of the crew.

757
00:58:43,339 --> 00:58:45,599
All right? Okay, so that's it!

758
00:58:45,599 --> 00:58:47,319
When you're done, go help your friends with the props.

759
00:58:47,319 --> 00:58:49,219
Because the security will come close the building.

760
00:58:49,219 --> 00:58:51,799
- All right? That's it!
- Okay.

761
00:58:51,799 --> 00:58:52,999
- See you there.
- See you.

762
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:56,779
- Let's go.
- Everyone, hurry up!

763
00:59:23,300 --> 00:59:25,380
It's all right.

764
00:59:25,900 --> 00:59:27,933
I won't do it.

765
00:59:35,420 --> 00:59:37,940
You should just do it.

766
00:59:37,940 --> 00:59:40,400
I know you want to.

767
00:59:40,400 --> 00:59:42,870
It's a play nominated for the contest.

768
00:59:45,980 --> 00:59:49,180
But I've given so much of our time to other people already.

769
00:59:57,960 --> 00:59:59,993
Teh.

770
00:59:59,993 --> 01:00:02,380
Since I've known you,

771
01:00:02,400 --> 01:00:05,520
your dream is making plays.

772
01:00:06,200 --> 01:00:09,460
And if you're not okay, how could I be okay?

773
01:00:12,820 --> 01:00:14,970
Then who are you going to be with?

774
01:00:16,260 --> 01:00:18,479
I'll just hang out with my friends, of course.

775
01:00:18,480 --> 01:00:19,799
When you're not around,

776
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:22,319
I'll go have a blast with my friends.

777
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:26,440
After this, I'll be partying at my friend's place.

778
01:00:45,320 --> 01:00:46,479
For real?

